<title>GERMANY: Germany's Metro sales up in first quarter.</title>
<headline>Germany's Metro sales up in first quarter.</headline>
<dateline>BONN 1997-05-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months to March 31:</p>
<p>(in millions of marks unless stated)</p>
<p>    Group sales				  14,889  vs 14,533</p>
<p>Of which:</p>
<p>     Metro wholesale			   2,415   vs 2,490</p>
<p>     Department stores			 2,729   vs 2,726</p>
<p>     Self-service department stores	2,548   vs 2,532</p>
<p>     Grocery stores			    1,918   vs 2,011</p>
<p>     Consumer electronics		    1,934   vs 1,679</p>
<p>     Building materials			1,007   vs 998</p>
<p>     Furniture				   379     vs 465</p>
<p>     Computers				   994     vs 776</p>
<p>     Clothing				    309     vs 290</p>
<p>     Shoes					 195     vs 180</p>
<p>     Mail-order				  125     vs 116</p>
<p>     Restaurants				 123     vs 120</p>
<p>     Others					214     vs 150</p>
<p>NOTE - Full name of the German retail group is Metro Holding AG. All figures are preliminary. The company said that when adjusted for the sales of BLV Grossverbraucher Service GmbH and small supermarkets, group sales rose 4.5 percent.</p>
<p>It said the first quarter figures were positively influenced by business at Easter.</p>
<p>&quot;Metro still expects no significant recovery of consumer demand in Germany in 1997,&quot; the company said in a statement.</p>
<p>-- Bonn Newsroom, 49 228 26097 150</p>
</text>
